The paper deals with representing vague information in Semantic Web languages, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of OWL 2 annotation properties to represent fuzzy ontologies also involves software engineering (cs.SE) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of ontologies, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
